title: Anna Vissi - Apagorevmeno (12/2008)
description:
Anna Vissi - Apagorevmeno

MP3 | CBR 320Kbps 44100 Stereo | 62:00 | 142 MB

"Apagorevmeno" is Greek singer Anna Vissi's 25th studio album, and was released on December 9, 2008 in Greece and Cyprus. The album is her first studio album in three years, and contains 13 songs, including the single "To Parelthon Mou" from the soundtrack of the film Bank Bang as a bonus song, as well as the Greek cover "Kontra", bringing the number of songs to 15. This will be Vissi's first album to not include any songs by Nikos Karvelas since her 1981 album Anna Vissi.
